<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Consume" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Consume,</orth> 1) trans. to devour, to destroy, to waste: <bibl n="shak. son 73.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 73, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 6, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.140" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 140</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.6.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 6, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.6.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 6, 78</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.137" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.71" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 1, 24</bibl>. Absolutely: <cit><quote>thy --ing canker,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.71" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 71</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ing sorrow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 61</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) refl. to perish, to dwindle: <cit><quote>fair flowers rot and c. themselves in little time,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 132" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 132</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou --st thyself in single life,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 9.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 9, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>virginity --s itself to the very paring,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.154" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 154</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) intr. to waste away, to pass away, to perish: <cit><quote>smoke from Aetna, that in air --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1042" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1042</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. away in sighs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. away in rust,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 1, 65</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. to ashes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.92" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 92</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fire and powder, which as they kiss c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.6.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 6, 11</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>